The paper deals with the foundations of quantum information and computation, which are interdisciplinary fields involving computer science, mathematics, and physics. The paper specifically focuses on the categorical foundations of quantum channels, which are mathematical objects used to describe the evolution of quantum systems. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), cs.QI (Quantum Physics), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Among these, cs.ET and cs.IT are the most likely categories, as they deal with new and emerging technologies and information theory, respectively, which are both relevant to quantum information and computation. cs.LO is also a likely category, as it deals with the logical foundations of computer science, which are relevant to the categorical foundations of quantum channels. cs.QI and cs.CC are less likely categories, as they are more specialized and may not be as directly relevant to the paper's focus on categorical foundations.
